{
  "number": 247,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/247",
  "title": "API Proposal: Theming draft",
  "body": "For a first version here's what theming could look like:\n- we have BEM classes in React Component (that's already mostly the case)\n- we have inline BEM classes in the default templates (without being able to override them, I think this is not necessary). For example `<span count=\"ais-refinementList..\"></span>`.\n- we create a default.css in themes/ that will do the minimum styling so that:\n  - it uses the BEM classes to style\n  - the default theme is usable\n  - it contains all the classes of the project, even if they are empty, so that a user can quickly copy paste it and tune it or understand it\n  - the default theme does no have too strong defaults, to be able to easily override them from a user.css\n- modify jsdelivr to be able to deploy css files\n- remove every css files from the instantsearch.js javascript, we will load them separately as <link> for now\n\nLet's not go right now into API needs to be able to override all the default templates (use case: bootstrap compliant markup + theme).\n",
